g.inkscape:label: Ctrl, Meta, Alt consistent across layers

text.tspan: Regardless of the layer, Ctrl, Meta, and Alt must remain as it. I.e. they must be available on all layers at the same
Arrows on hjkl (matching vim) for L2
Continuation of the numbers row under the last number
due to the row end on L1. This make it easy to remember
as it is ideologically consistent with the numbers row
Numbers remain on the top row under the L1 to be consistent with the regular row above the top alphabetical row. Shift makes the numbers into corresponding symbols same as on the regular layout
